author: Shannon Molloy
title: Move over MKR and The Bachelorette — these are the shock ratings hits of TV you won’t believe
text:
WHETHER it’s big budget dramas or personality driven cooking shows, the big hitters of television are well known.
But among the likes of My Kitchen Rules and 800 Words are several unexpected names — little quiet achievers that bring in strong numbers without being too showy about it.
Here are the surprise hits of the small screen.
Strong performer ... Gruen on the ABC regularly nudges one million viewers each week — a stellar result. Picture: Supplied
Friday fun ... Better Homes and Gardens, with Johanna Griggs, is an audience favourite. Picture: Supplied
Strong performer ... the show about drunk drivers, RBT, regularly does well for Nine on a Thursday. Picture: Supplied
Popular drama ... The Doctor Blake Mysteries stars Craig McLachlan. Picture: Supplied
Real drama ... Kings Cross ER, about the busy St Vincent’s Hospital, is a solid performer for Nine. Picture: Supplied
New hit ... world surfing champion Layne Beachley narrates Beach Cops, a Seven ob-doc about police on Sydney’s northern beaches. Picture: Supplied
Brit crime ... David Walliams as Tommy and Jessica Raine as Tuppence in Partners In Crime. Picture: Supplied
Nice nature ... Costa Georgiadis in Gardening Australia, which often does well for the ABC on a Saturday. Picture: Supplied
Surprise performer ... given it airs on a Sunday, British crime drama Vera does pretty well in the ratings. Picture: Supplied
Trouble arrivals ... Seven’s ob-doc Border Security has long been an audience favourite. Picture: Supplied
